# --- Created by Python / uv install (never commit) ---
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
# uv lockfile is regenerated by `uv sync` / `uv lock`
uv.lock

# --- Local tooling ---
.serena/
.DS_Store

# --- Claude Code / AI assistant files (never commit; kept local only) ---
.claude/
CLAUDE.md
CLAUDE.local.md
.mcp.json

# --- Local secrets / machine config ---
.env
credentials.json
secrets/
.tokens/

# --- Generated data ---
# Atomic-write temp files (a crashed run may leave one behind; the workflows
# `git add data/...` whole folders, so these must never be committable).
*.part

# Isolated output root for the manual pilot test (docs/ndvi/PILOT_TEST.md).
data_pilot/

# Heavy raw/intermediate rasters are regenerated by the pipeline; never committed
# (hundreds of MB to GBs). The GitHub Actions workflows commit back only the small
# deliverable folders listed below, so E1.3 can reuse E1.1's lookup CSV and E1.2 can
# reuse its NDVI baseline without re-downloading / rebuilding.
data/01_raw_africa_monthly/
data/02_clip/
data/03_seasonal_totals/

# Local-only farmer registry (PII). Never committed; CI uses the tracked demo
# docs/sample_ndvi_farmers.csv (the default of config.NDVI_FARMERS_CSV).
# Exception: baseline_plots.csv (the E1.2 baseline-donor plot registry) IS
# tracked - phone numbers are stripped from it, and CI needs it to rebuild the
# sector baseline (config.NDVI_PLOTS_REGISTRY).
data/farmers/*
!data/farmers/baseline_plots.csv

# All NDVI outputs are REGENERATED by a run (ndvi/registry -> baseline -> current)
# and the real E1.2 deliverable is the Google Sheet + the Drive run archive, not the
# repo - so nothing under data/ndvi/ is committed: normalized manifests, the sector
# baseline CSVs, per-cycle logs, per-run imagery folders and smoke-test scratch files
# are all rebuilt on demand (the donor registry below is the only tracked input).
# CI uploads the logs/run folder as a workflow artifact instead of committing them.
data/ndvi/

# Tracked deliverables (everything else under data/ is committed by the workflows):
#   data/00_boundary/   closed boundary polygon        (E1.1)
#   data/04_average/    multi-year average raster      (E1.1)
#   data/05_tables/     rainfall lookup CSV + scores   (E1.1)
#   data/pilot_check/   pilot sign-off package         (E1.3)
# E1.2 commits no data: its baseline is rebuilt each run, outputs go to Sheet/Drive.
